name: Ffionaâ€™s Restaurant
address: 51 Kensington Church Street, London W8 4BA, United Kingdom
author: James L.
description:
Nice little restaurant. It is small with only 5 tables and they fill up fast with reservations. I was able to secure one seat for myself on a Thursday night about 7pm. But she turned away everyone else that came in because of reservations. 

Nice assortment of menu items. I was searching for fish & chips to eat and they had it. This was very good. Wine and cocktail selection is great. Beer selection was very small. 

Staff was exceedingly friendly. It was like I was eating in her own house. Fun place.
